# gstack

This project uses [gstack](https://github.com/garrytan/gstack) for structured AI workflows. Global install: `~/.cursor/skills/gstack`.

## Web browsing

Use the **/browse** skill from gstack for all web browsing and browser automation. Do not use Chrome MCP tools (`mcp__claude-in-chrome__*` or similar).

## When to use gstack

- **New idea or feature** → `/office-hours`, then `/plan-ceo-review` or `/autoplan`
- **Before building** → `/plan-eng-review`, `/plan-design-review` as appropriate
- **After code changes** → `/review`
- **Test a URL** → `/qa <url>`
- **Ship a PR** → `/ship`
- **Upgrade gstack** → `/gstack-upgrade`

## Available skills (short names)

`/office-hours`, `/plan-ceo-review`, `/plan-eng-review`, `/plan-design-review`, `/plan-devex-review`, `/design-consultation`, `/design-shotgun`, `/design-html`, `/review`, `/ship`, `/land-and-deploy`, `/canary`, `/benchmark`, `/browse`, `/open-gstack-browser`, `/qa`, `/qa-only`, `/design-review`, `/setup-browser-cookies`, `/setup-deploy`, `/setup-gbrain`, `/sync-gbrain`, `/retro`, `/investigate`, `/document-release`, `/document-generate`, `/codex`, `/cso`, `/autoplan`, `/pair-agent`, `/careful`, `/freeze`, `/guard`, `/unfreeze`, `/gstack-upgrade`, `/learn`

When a gstack skill applies, invoke it rather than improvising the same workflow from scratch.
